Description: Two-joining sherds of lower wall of North Ionian pottery bowl; interior glazed with added red band lined in white; exterior orientation uncertain: maeander band between bands; above or below uncertain motif, not obviously animal or floral; graffito on inside.
Curator's comments: Marked in pencil '9' (?) and 'List 43' on label.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1202)
